explains: adj. 可辨认的；可认明的；可证明是同一的

sentences.en: The house is easily identifiable by the large tree outside.
sentences.cn: 这房子很容易从外面的这棵大树辨认出来。

sentences.en: They become less identifiable, more generalizable to any audience.
sentences.cn: 它们变得更难以识别，更容易被所有观众接受。

sentences.en: Privacy law builds on the concept of damage to an individual from identifiable knowledge about them.
sentences.cn: 隐私权法建立在个人可识别信息受到伤害这一概念之上。
